# Vendored third-party content: pin to LF so the working copy stays
# byte-identical to its upstream source on every platform, regardless of
# core.autocrlf (which is `true` on Windows checkouts). Without this a
# fresh Windows checkout rewrites these to CRLF, breaking the "byte-for-byte
# from upstream" property the vendoring relies on. See TEMPLATE-CHANGELOG
# v2.4.8. Scoped deliberately — repo-wide line-ending policy is a separate
# call, not made here.
profiles/typescript-next/skills/frontend-design/** text eol=lf

# Parity-tested mirror pairs must materialize IDENTICALLY on every
# platform: base/.gitattributes (v2.6.0) pins base/** to LF, so its
# byte-for-byte twins — harness-kit/ and the root-homed SETUP.md — need
# the same pin, or a fresh Windows checkout (autocrlf=true) writes CRLF
# on one side only and test_kit_parity reads phantom drift. Still scoped:
# the repo-wide line-ending call remains unmade.
harness-kit/** text=auto eol=lf
/SETUP.md text eol=lf
